claim.claim-text:
1. A method for preparing monolayers of cells, comprising the following steps: 
culturing a cellular monolayer on at least one SCS; 
cooling each SCS together with the cellular monolayer in such a way that the formation of ice crystals in the cells of the monolayer is avoided; 
substituting the cellular water in the cells of the monolayer; and 
embedding the cellular monolayer together with the SCS in such a way that the cells of the cellular monolayer on the SCS are surrounded by embedding material, and the SCS is substantially free of embedding material.
